{"id":625,"date":"2022-02-23T14:07:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-23T12:07:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=625"},"modified":"2022-03-23T21:49:42","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T19:49:42","slug":"how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/","title":{"rendered":"Boost Your Revenue with BaaS: How to Use Banking as a Service"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Banking as a service, commonly abbreviated as Baas, enables nonbanks to provide financial services to their clients. They do this by building on the APIs provided by banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The model allows Fintech companies to build new products on existing banking infrastructure. Without it, it would not be possible to offer the said services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Traditionally, companies need a license to offer banking services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, a company looking to boost its business revenue by providing deposit and loan services will need:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Pre-paid instrument license: It is a license you must have to issue pre-paid cards<br>\u2022 NBFC license: A license for offering loans and lending assets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As things stand, licenses are pretty hard to obtain. This is where Baas comes in for the rescue.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"item-673d6643b58a5\" aria-label=\"Table of Content\"><span style=\"display: flex;align-items: center;width: 35px;height: 30px;justify-content: center;direction:ltr;\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\