h Companies<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/#2-offer-their-clients-debit-and-credit-cards\" title=\"2. Offer Their Clients Debit and Credit Cards\">2. Offer Their Clients Debit and Credit Cards<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/#3-offer-loans-and-lend-assets-to-customers\" title=\"3. Offer Loans and Lend Assets to Customers\">3. Offer Loans and Lend Assets to Customers<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/#4-offer-investment-services-to-the-consumers\" title=\"4. Offer Investment Services to the Consumers\">4. Offer Investment Services to the Consumers<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/#5-assist-in-verifying-customer-information\" title=\"5. Assist in Verifying Customer Information\">5. Assist in Verifying Customer Information<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-baas\/#what-makes-banking-as-a-service-useful\" title=\"What Makes Banking as a Service Useful?\">What Makes Banking as a Service Useful?<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2 id=\"banking-as-a-service-what-is-it\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"banking-as-a-service-what-is-it\"><\/span>Banking as a Service: What Is It?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.finextra.com\/blogposting\/20099\/what-the-hell-is-banking-as-a-service-and-what-is-it-not\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">banking as a service<\/a> model allows non-financial institutions to integrate with banks. Thanks to this integration, they can now begin to facilitate digital payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nonbanks like this model as it allows them to boost business revenue without going through the motions of acquiring a banking license.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But how does it work? And who are the players involved?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"players-involved-in-baas\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"players-involved-in-baas\"><\/span>Players Involved in Baas<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It generally involves three chief players:<br><br><strong>1. The Bank: New-Age or Traditional Bank<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They are responsible for providing the infrastructure as a service layer (IaaS). It comprises physical infrastructure services, e.g., communication and server hardware.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Banks possess the licenses required to offer banking services. Through this model, they get to open up their banking systems to third-party providers.<br><br><strong>2. Banking as a Service Platform<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The platform offers the software needed to ensure safe data transmission between the fintech company and the bank. It\u2019s a layer known as the middle layer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Companies supporting <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/#:~:text=Anyone%20looking%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20to%20a%20global%20scale%20should%20consider%20whether%20their%20current%20payment%20provider%20can%20handle%20such%20a%20shift\">digital payments and payment<\/a> processing link into the platform like Lego. The platform is purely API-based and serves as a back-end for nonbanks.<br><br><strong>3. Fintech Startups and Nonbanks<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are the companies that interact with the consumers. They also serve as the platform\u2019s primary customers.<br>Please note that the companies in this category can be fintech on non-fintech. They only need to be interested in connecting their products to these financial services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The companies need to comply with the existing regulations to plug into the platform. Non-compliance means they cannot facilitate digital payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-to-boost-revenue\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"how-to-use-banking-as-a-service-to-boost-revenue\"><\/span>How to Use Banking as a Service to Boost Revenue<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Baas is a model that is currently being implemented across several industries. Significant use cases of this model include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"1-online-banking-by-fintech-and-non-fintech-companies\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1-online-banking-by-fintech-and-non-fintech-companies\"><\/span>1. Online Banking by Fintech and Non-Fintech Companies<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Baas can allow fintech and non-fintech companies to offer digital banking services. They can shift their focus to service providers instead of concentrating on bank licenses.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The end products are usually user-friendly and more technologically advanced. It makes them better than the standard products offered by traditional banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, the companies can develop apps to help consumers track their savings, account balances, and daily transactions. They can also:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I. Ensure customers have quick access to their funds whenever they need them<br>II. Do away with hidden fees to guarantee a better customer experience<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"2-offer-their-clients-debit-and-credit-cards\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"2-offer-their-clients-debit-and-credit-cards\"><\/span>2. Offer Their Clients Debit and Credit Cards<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, the Baas model allows non-fintech companies to offer their customers credit and debit cards. Consumers can use the mobile app to get real-time updates of all their transactions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All account details, including recent payments and deposits, are displayed in a user-friendly manner. Companies looking to boost business revenue can do so by lowering their rates.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Interestingly, most companies have started to offer their customers cashback offers. The offers apply to both credit and debit cardholders.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To increase customer satisfaction, the companies can offer cashback offers as assets without expiry. Or they could also apply to several products purchased through the apps, website, or in-store.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/payment_regulation_1.jpg\" alt=\"Digital Banking\" class=\"wp-image-219\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/payment_regulation_1.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/payment_regulation_1-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/payment_regulation_1-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"3-offer-loans-and-lend-assets-to-customers\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"3-offer-loans-and-lend-assets-to-customers\"><\/span>3. Offer Loans and Lend Assets to Customers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Baas makes it possible for businesses to lend funds and assets to loyal customers. For example, a travel agent can provide one-click loans to travellers to guarantee uninterrupted travel.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Such a loan would also assist in improving the customer experience.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this model, businesses can provide their customers with options such as \u201cBuy Now, Pay Later.\u201d Such options should allow clients to choose their preferred payment model.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The inbuilt app should allow clients to track all their monthly repayments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"4-offer-investment-services-to-the-consumers\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"4-offer-investment-services-to-the-consumers\"><\/span>4. Offer Investment Services to the Consumers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Assisting customers to automate finance and investment services is another way digital payments companies can use this platform.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They can allow their clients to obtain <a href=\"https:\/\/www.finextra.com\/pressarticle\/90458\/scalable-capital-reduces-minimum-investment-amount-and-raises-sustainability-standards\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">custom-made investment<\/a> options with low-cost index funds. This would include automatically rebalancing the client portfolio.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"5-assist-in-verifying-customer-information\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-assist-in-verifying-customer-information\"><\/span>5. Assist in Verifying Customer Information<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Payment transfer and processing errors can cause an organization to lose its reputation. In some cases, it could cause a merchant to lose business, especially when the problem recurs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The verification of banking information can assist in eliminating and preventing such errors. The platform can assist in verifying customer information before the payment process can begin.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can prove helpful when processing bulk payments across multiple payment channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-makes-banking-as-a-service-useful\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-makes-banking-as-a-service-useful\"><\/span>What Makes Banking as a Service Useful?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The model has assisted in solving several issues within the fintech industry. For example:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 It helps unlock banking: Fintech and non-fintech companies that want to offer banking services typically have to meet stringent requirements, e.g., securing a license. By plugging into the banks\u2019 system via an API, fintech companies can access the features they need to build a digital payments platform.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 It\u2019s great for consumers: Consumers are on the lookout for better experiences. These are things that traditional banks cannot offer. Baas allows them access to the experiences they desire.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the challenges of implementing banking as a service are plenty, its use cases can help a company boost its revenue. Its solutions additionally pave the way for user-friendly products.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Banking as a service, commonly abbreviated as Baas, enables nonbanks to provide financial services to their clients. They do this by building on the APIs provided by banks. The model allows Fintech companies to build new products on existing banking infrastructure. Without it, it would not be possible to offer the said services. Traditionally, companies [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":656,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16,25],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/625"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=625"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/625\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":658,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/625\/revisions\/658"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/w